              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 0.6125 MeV deuterons on 0.5 milli-gram/cm2",
                "titanium tritide target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural uranium sample,thickness=1 milli-gram/cm2,",
                "area=6x6 mm2,electroplated on 0.2 mm thick aluminium",
                "backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct detection of fission fragments"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 87x10 mm2 Mica detector surrounding the fission",
                "sample used for fragment measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Least square Legendre fit for angular distribution,",
                "Legendre-coefficients of the form",
                "   W(theta)=sum(a(l)*p(l))",
                "Theta is the angle of the fragment with respect to the",
                "incident neutrons in the centre-of-mass system. As the",
                "angular distribution is symmetric at 90 degrees, only",
                "even terms occur in the polynomial."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission fragments"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Data have been corrected for the definite size of",
                "fission sample and detector, and the fragment detection",
                "efficiency difference in different angles. The neutron",
                "source was regarded as a point source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Errors given in the data Table are only",
                "statistical.",
                "The energy resolution is due to the energy spread of",
                "deuterons and the angle subtended by the fission sample"
              ]
